        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 6:26PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 622 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Summerville, moving
east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Heavy rain may cause temporary street flooding especially
in poor drainage areas. Some street flooding has already
been noted in low lying areas of Summerville.

Locations impacted include...
Summerville, Trion, Lyerly, Menlo, Cloudland, Berryton, and James H.
Floyd State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.  Electrical
appliances should not be used unless in an emergency. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
